This paper deals with the privacy guarantees of encrypted DNS, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The proposed traffic analysis method involves modeling DNS sequences, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.MM) or data mining (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the privacy implications of encrypted DNS, which could be relevant to the subfield of cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY).
